message: Move maintainer field to be under branch
Link to Swift.org for project list

Rename check to project_precommit_check.

This makes it clearer that the purpose of this script is a precommit check that a project/updated project is ready for submission to the source compat suite.
Update README describing project compatibility format changes
Update README for check script changes
Update README to use 4.2 Swift version

Add support for xfailing based on build configuration (release vs debug)

We have a project failing only in release configuration at the moment with no
existing way to xfail only release.

This change also reworks how xfail matching works to be more expressive, since
it could previously only match either branches or platforms for a specific
compatibility version, not both. See the README.md changes for details.

Migrated projects.json to the new structure (projects-incremental.json has no
xfails currently) and updated the starscream xfail to be release-only, but
left support for the old structure to allow time to update the json in
downstream repos.
Update the scripts to use main branch
Add README entry how to only XFail the Source Comapat CI job
Update the issues to GitHub urls
drop a note on the readme about python 3.8 support from #681
